name: Kroger
comment: Every kroger business allows trans people to use the restroom of their choosing, whether it is single stalled, or multistalled. :-)

name: Amorino Gelato
directions: In the back, left of the register/counter.
comment: Don't need to buy anything, can just head straight in.

name: White Buffalo Restaurant
directions: Go to the actual restaurant, to the desk, and turn left to get to the back.
comment: The staff are really friendly. If you cannot find the bathroom, just ask.

name: Krogers grocery store
directions: By the pharmacy

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the Starbucks

name: Haywards ice cream
directions: Right side of the building
comment: Only open seasonally and during business hours.

name: Lyman Community Library
directions: In the lobby, take the door on the right. The bathroom is on the left.
comment: I volunteer at this library. The librarian is very friendly and open-minded.

name: Jamestown Riverfront Amenities Pavilion
directions: It is near the Jamestown dock with the ships.
comment: It is a family/accesible bathroom, no stalls, one room with a door you can lock.

name: Westbranch outlets
directions: 128 in the outlets at westbranch

name: STAP
directions: Large house across from Synagogue
comment: Just ask the front desk to use the restroom, it's a safe space.

name: STAP - Prevention
directions: Front door surrounded by like green trim.
comment: Just ask to use the restroom, the people there are very open.

name: Kroger
directions: Near pharmacy

name: Studio 1212
directions: In through the back entrance of the building, then straight ahead and to the right on the wall once you're inside.
comment: I think you have to be using/renting the space at the time to use their bathroom.

name: Lingo Cafe & Bar
comment: Unisex, single stalls

name: Schnippers
comment: There are three single-person restrooms. You need to be a paying customer; the access code is on the receipt.

name: 9750 S Maryland Pkwy  Smiths
directions: It's in the front end. They have male and female separate, but also a male and female single stall together.

name: Gus' Pretzels
directions: Single unisex bathroom to the right of the checkout counter down a very short hallway
comment: Try the pretzels, they are yum!

name: Tri-County Chiropractic of St Marys
directions: All the way down the hallway, last door on the left
comment: Ask the receptionist if you can use the restroom

name: Mojo Coffee Gallery
directions: To the right as soon as you walk in!
comment: No need for purchase, it's just in the foyer

name: Ben and Jerry's
comment: May need to be a customer

name: University Commons
directions: enter through the front door and turn right then head past the double doors to the restrooms
comment:
card access required at times, after 11 pm. also required during high risk times 
for srudents

name: Indiana Blood Center
comment: Clients only (I don't know many trans people who donate blood, but I thought I'd map it just in case)

name: GG Brown Bldg
directions: By main hallway to DOW bldg. adjacent to room 1630

name: Starbucks
comment: Kind staff. LGTBQ Welcoming.

name: Del Taco
comment: It says you need cashier assistance but they're always open regardless

name: Jo-Ann Fabrics and Crafts
directions: Back of the store, far right

name: Gay City Health Project
directions: Up ramp in Gay City Auditorium (large room directly across from entrance)

name: Pettirosso Seattle
directions: In back next to Kitchen
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms. You probably need to be a paying customer, since they're in back.

name: Tavistock Clinic
directions:
2 bathrooms. 1) 3rd floor in the GIDS department, past the waiting room
2) ground floor and end of main corridor take a left so you see the library sign. Walk down and it will be labelled on your right.
comment: Just ask if you are unsure of where you are going, and it doesn't need to intimidate you just because it's a clinic. you can go in just use the toilets it's fine. ;)

name: Pete's Coffee
comment: 2 gender neutral bathrooms

name: Trillium Health
directions: In care management office and in the clinic.

name: Vancouver Public LIbrary - nə́c̓aʔmat ct Branch
Pierce College
directions: Rainer Building - 3rd floor, side A, across from room 361a

name: Vancouver Public Library - Mount Pleasant Branch
Vancouver Public Library - Terry Salman Branch
Target
directions: To the right of the enterance

name: Regal Meridian 16
directions: First floor, under "ADA Restrooms" sign in lobby
comment: There are two single-occupancy restrooms marked gender neutral

name: Bagley Hall Chemistry Building
directions: Ground floor (marked on elevator). We had to go down a floor from the level with the entrance.
comment: Disability accessible gender neutral restroom

name: Faz's Tex Max
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Temple Coffee Roasters
directions: In the back hallway past the coffee bar
comment: You probably need to be a paying customer and you have to ask for a key

name: Midway Cafe
directions: Opposite side of the room from bar seating/stage area in the back

name: REWE
directions: By the entrance

name: 202 East Main St. /Dundee Library/Dundee public library
directions: Go into the library, not the town hall, there are two doors, ask one of the staff members for the bathroom key.

name: Lowe's
directions: In the front of the store with the regular restrooms; just to the right of the Men's room.

name: Aroma Espresso Bar
comment: Paying customers but they make a mean latte.

name: Bob Evans Restaurant
directions: Straight back from main entrance, it's the family restroom.
comment: Anyone can use, don't have to be a paying customer

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back turn to the left
comment: Two bathrooms, both very big and gender neutral

name: Tacoma Mall
directions: In good court. Currently next to Flaming Wok
comment: Has adult and child toilet, adult and child sink, and changing table

name: University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, Morrill Hall
directions: Ground floor, by the elevator near the north entrance and the loading dock access.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store
comment: You have to ask for the bathroom code and are supposed to be a paying customer

name: Cape Lookout Harker's Island
directions: Family restroom is parking lot adjacent

name: Harker's Island Cape Lookout
directions: Family restroom off parking lot

name: Fish City
directions: Ground floor of restaurant, to the back on/at the left. Accessible bathroom, no assistance/unlocking required from staff
comment: You would need to be a paying customer

name: Fish City
directions: Ground floor, to the left of the till / kitchen
comment: You would need to be a paying diner

name: Reval Cafe
directions: Upstairs
comment: Customers only. Not accessible. One toilet

name: University of the Pacific
directions: In the cafeteria on the first floor on your way out of the right side there are two gender neutral single stall bathrooms.
comment: Act like you are a college student or faculty member.

name: Tully's Coffee
comment: You have to be a paying customer, just ask for the code.

name: Psi Upsilon Fraternity
directions: Two single stalls downstairs.
comment: For guests of the Haus only.

name: Tesoro
directions: Corner of Pegar Rd and Davis Rd. Restroom is down the hallway to the right.

name: Flo's Cafe
directions: the easiest way to get to these is to walk through the front entrance and go to the right. there is an arrow pointing out two doors and there are two single restrooms marked "companion."

name: Tri-Valley High School
directions: Band locker hallway, special needs room. Can be a locker room replacement as well.
comment: You must be a student or faculty member

name: Revelstoke public washrooms
comment: Not single stall, but two stalled and easy to slip in and out quickly. There is also a wheelchair accessible/nursing/diaper changing restroom available. All are safe spaces.

name: LA Nails
comment: Paying costomers

name: Yonge Egligton Centre
directions: Across from the Metro store.
comment: Usually clean

name: Epcot world showcase
directions: Bathrooms as you exit France
comment: Paying customer in Epcot

name: Groundwork Coffee
directions: Enter from outside; you need a code from the barista

name: Caribou Coffee
directions: In the back, to the left of the barista station
comment: Paying customers or guests of paying customers have access

name: Sidecar Coffee Shop
directions: Near the back entrance, past the barista station
comment: The single stalls are gendered, but the environment is typically pretty open if you need to use either one.

name: UNI-Dome
directions: There are two inclusive, accessible restrooms in the tunnel between the UNI-Dome and the WRC: Rooms 118 and 121

name: Strayer-Wood Theatre
directions: Room 123, right near the ticket office

name: Dunkin Dounuts
directions: At the back entrance

name: Platform 1094
directions: Go round to the back of the building and follow the signs

name: The Public Theater
directions: Walk to the back left of the lobby, past the information desk.
comment: Bathrooms are gendered but with the explicit signage that anyone can use the restroom of their choice. During show hours, a gender neutral bathroom can be requested of the house staff. Lobby bathrooms are open to the general public all day.

name: Burgerville
comment: Two bathrooms, both with changing stations, both handicapped accessible.

name: Cole Park
directions: By the splash pad, there is a male and female restroom but no one will harass you there.
comment: I can't vouge for people staring but you won't be stopped for using either bathroom.

name: Ryerson Students Union
directions: Second floor to the left of the microwave
